abstract: National Assn of Realtors reports that its pending home sales index rose 0.9 percent to 112.6 in May, highest level in over nine years; figure is positive sign for housing market and broader economy.
lead_paragraph: The National Association of Realtors said that its pending home sales index, based on contracts signed in May, increased 0.9 percent to a reading of 112.6.

headline.main: Pending Home Sales Rise to Highest Level in 9 Years
headline.print_headline: In Sign of Strength for Economy, Pending Home Sales Hit Nine-Year High
